2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 354
BY REPRESENTATIVE DESHOTEL
UTILITIES: Urges and requests the Public Service Commission to study incorporating
Louisiana One Call as a state agency
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Public Service Commission to study the feasibility and potential
3 benefits of incorporating Louisiana One Call and 811 services into a dedicated state
4 division or office for the purpose of improving underground utility coordination,
5 mapping, damage prevention, public safety, and infrastructure planning, and to report
6 its findings to the legislature.
7 WHEREAS, Louisiana's underground infrastructure network continues to expand
8 rapidly due to broadband deployment, water and sewer improvements, electric and gas
9 infrastructure upgrades, and transportation projects; and
10 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Underground Utilities and Facilities Damage Prevention
11 Law, R.S. 40:1749.11 et seq., establishes requirements for notification and coordination
12 prior to excavation activities in order to protect underground facilities and public safety; and
13 WHEREAS, Louisiana One Call, commonly known through the 811 system, plays
14 a critical role in facilitating communication between excavators and utility operators to
15 reduce damage to underground infrastructure; and
16 WHEREAS, increased infrastructure activity across the state has highlighted the
17 growing importance of utility coordination, accurate locating, mapping, and enforcement
18 efforts; and
19 WHEREAS, damage to underground utilities can result in disruptions to essential
20 services, public safety risks, increased costs to taxpayers and utilities, and delays to critical
21 infrastructure projects; and
